**who —** The NTSC Signal — the picture itself · ethereal

**what —** the picture itself · ethereal

**where —** NES · THE NES (exereunesis · the teardown)  Framework inputs: chip; bus; spec  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The 2C02 generates composite video directly: ~240 visible scanlines at ~60 fields per second, in a palette built for a CRT. The image was the chip's native output — there was no frame buffer to read back.

**how —** Rendered from the public technical record.

**◌ the mythos —** The 2C02 generates composite video directly: ~240 visible scanlines at ~60 fields per second, in a palette built for a CRT. The image was the chip's native output — there was no frame buffer to read back. a part of the machine

